WEBVTT

00:06.210 --> 00:08.201
[theme music playing]

00:30.110 --> 00:32.351
[Hannah] It's a giant fucking universe.

00:34.320 --> 00:36.902
[Clay] It is a giant universe.

00:38.200 --> 00:41.363
[Hannah] Like, how are we supposed to do
anything significant?

00:41.450 --> 00:43.953
Anything that means anything?
We're not even clots.

00:44.960 --> 00:47.918
But, somehow,
every day feels like life or death, right?

00:48.630 --> 00:51.758
Even though, at some level,
it also feels like nothing matters at all.

00:52.840 --> 00:54.080
Or means anything.

00:54.920 --> 00:59.038
And, like, in a real way, we're all just
accidents of birth, you know?

00:59.470 --> 01:02.928
Like, it's just dumb luck
that we're not having this conversation

01:03.020 --> 01:04.920
somewhere much worse than this basement.

01:05.020 --> 01:10.936
Like, some shantytown in South Asia,
or the frozen north of Iceland,

01:11.020 --> 01:14.023
or a burning desert in Africa.

01:14.900 --> 01:16.106
But that's it.

01:16.200 --> 01:20.523
We are exactly who we are,
in this moment, in this place,

01:20.620 --> 01:22.281
and I think that matters.

01:23.080 --> 01:26.538
Because without you, without me,
everything is different.

01:27.500 --> 01:29.741
I don't know if anything
would be different without me.

01:30.340 --> 01:31.409
I would be different.

01:32.300 --> 01:33.949
Okay, if I do something, it affects you.

01:34.300 --> 01:38.009
Makes you do something that affects,
I don't know, Alex Standall,

01:38.090 --> 01:40.888
who affects Jessica Davis.

01:41.140 --> 01:47.090
[Clay] Who affects Justin Foley,
then Zach Dempsey, then Mrs. Bradley,

01:47.190 --> 01:50.227
-and then Tony Padilla...
-[Hannah] And on and on.

01:50.770 --> 01:52.510
[Clay] It's huge if you think about it.

01:52.980 --> 01:54.971
[Hannah] It's an infinite universe.

01:56.400 --> 01:57.446
[Clay] Infinity.

01:58.280 --> 02:00.157
It's funny we have a word
for that concept,

02:00.240 --> 02:02.697
but there's no way we can understand it.

02:03.790 --> 02:08.033
-Maybe... love?
-Love?

02:09.420 --> 02:12.162
Maybe love is how you understand infinity.

02:13.500 --> 02:16.549
When your love has no limit.
When it goes on forever.

02:17.840 --> 02:20.252
Maybe that feels like infinity.

02:21.470 --> 02:23.847
Yeah. Maybe.

02:26.600 --> 02:28.761
[alarm clock ringing]

02:34.520 --> 02:35.350
[Clay] Hey, Slqe.

02:37.440 --> 02:39.567
It's, uh... It's me again.

02:41.450 --> 02:43.577
Clay. Calling you.

02:45.490 --> 02:48.994
Nothing much new to report.
I go to court today.

02:51.710 --> 02:55.089
To testify. For Hannah.

02:58.170 --> 03:00.001
Still dealing with Justin.

03:01.630 --> 03:02.676
This is weird.

03:04.760 --> 03:07.593
You should have some pancakes.
They're fucking amazing.

03:08.520 --> 03:09.475
[Matt] I'll get you a plate.

03:12.400 --> 03:14.436
Clay, your dad's going to take you
to court today.

03:15.570 --> 03:16.889
[exhales] Great.

03:17.480 --> 03:19.983
-I wish I could be there as well.
-Rea|ly no problem.

03:20.190 --> 03:23.489
I've got this.
And you've got alt-Clay here, so...

03:26.950 --> 03:29.248
But, I mean, things are actually great.

03:30.460 --> 03:31.654
I'm glad to be going to court,

03:31.750 --> 03:34.241
and I really think it's going to be
a good way to get closure.

03:40.220 --> 03:43.462
Yeah, I'm really looking forward
to being done with all this.

03:45.680 --> 03:46.635
I love you.

03:47.970 --> 03:49.380
Call me. Bye.

03:52.390 --> 03:55.439
[Mrs. Standall]
Alex, honey? Wake up. Wake up.

03:56.020 --> 03:58.932
-Alexander.
-What? What happened?

03:59.400 --> 04:01.948
-Sorry, you were sleeping so soundly.
-[sighs]

04:02.740 --> 04:06.198
Sorry, I was dreaming about running.

04:08.530 --> 04:09.656
Happy birthday.

04:11.370 --> 04:13.531
-Oh, wow.
-[laughs]

04:13.620 --> 04:16.077
Right. Thanks.

04:16.960 --> 04:20.919
So I heard from Peter,
and he is driving down this afternoon

04:21.010 --> 04:22.375
to be here in time for the party.

04:22.880 --> 04:23.835
Oh.

04:24.300 --> 04:26.086
Do we have to have a party?

04:26.800 --> 04:29.803
But it's all booked,
and your father got his shift off.

04:29.890 --> 04:31.346
Haven't you told your friends?

04:31.930 --> 04:36.799
Well, yeah, I mean... Plus, they got
your e-vite with the bunnies on it.

04:38.110 --> 04:42.183
-You not feeling up to it?
-No, I am. I totally am.

04:42.690 --> 04:44.567
Good. We'll have fun.

04:44.650 --> 04:46.652
All right. Get yourself up,
do your stretches.

04:46.740 --> 04:49.982
[gasps] And I have a new hemp milk to try.
It's delicious.

04:51.740 --> 04:52.946
[door closes]

04:57.210 --> 04:58.029
[sighs]

05:02.420 --> 05:04.217
You should come _
for a morning run next time.

05:04.300 --> 05:06.757
[chuckles]
I don't run unless I'm being chased.

05:07.470 --> 05:09.040
And even then, I don't run.

05:10.310 --> 05:11.846
You ran pretty fast last night.

05:12.930 --> 05:15.307
Yeah, uh... I'm sorry.

05:15.390 --> 05:17.301
I got a text from Mrs. Baker,
and I had to go--

05:17.400 --> 05:18.594
No excuses needed.

05:20.770 --> 05:23.147
Look, I don't wanna tie you down.

05:23.650 --> 05:25.732
And I don't want you to think
you owe me anything.

05:28.110 --> 05:32.069
But I like you. A lot, I think.

05:43.380 --> 05:44.836
-I'm done early tonight.
-Hmm.

05:44.920 --> 05:46.251
No self-defense class.

05:48.680 --> 05:53.049
-That's quite a group you got there.
-Yeah. Yeah, right?

05:53.850 --> 05:57.434
The, uh, the guy with no eye,
what's his deal?

05:58.350 --> 05:59.840
I don't know, really.

06:00.270 --> 06:03.353
He got beat pretty bad a while back.
I think it was mugging or something.

06:03.940 --> 06:05.646
He takes a few classes.

06:05.740 --> 06:08.026
I think he's working through the PTSD
from the assault.

06:09.160 --> 06:10.400
Seems pretty haunted by it.

06:11.660 --> 06:12.479
Jesus.

06:15.290 --> 06:17.861
-Does he remember much?
-Haven't spoken to him about it.

06:18.460 --> 06:21.532
-There's lots of stories in that class.
-I bet.

06:22.670 --> 06:25.047
Aren't we going the wrong way
for your first period?

06:25.130 --> 06:27.371
Uh, I thought we'd take
the long way today.

06:28.930 --> 06:30.921
-Why is Zach waiting for us?
-[chuckles]

06:31.930 --> 06:36.845
-And why is he smiling like that? What?
-[laughs]

06:37.980 --> 06:42.644
-Wait, is it your birthday?
-[Jessica] Whoo!

06:42.730 --> 06:43.970
-What?
-What?

06:44.070 --> 06:45.970
[Zach, Jessica laugh]

06:46.070 --> 06:49.278
-You guys got a banner made?
-It was a group project.

06:49.360 --> 06:53.319
I made the design, Clay ordered it online,
and Zach put it up.

06:53.910 --> 06:54.979
Wow, that's...

06:57.250 --> 06:59.366
[chuckles] ...that's really, really nice,
you guys.

06:59.960 --> 07:01.245
[Bryce] Aw.

07:02.460 --> 07:04.087
Happy birthday, buddy.

07:04.460 --> 07:06.451
Oh, sweet banner.

07:06.880 --> 07:08.199
Is your mom bringing cupcakes?

07:08.300 --> 07:10.336
I hope she brings enough
for the whole class.

07:10.430 --> 07:12.330
Maybe you'll get a new cane
this year too, huh?

07:12.430 --> 07:14.421
[chuckling] Yeah.

07:14.510 --> 07:15.807
And some new friends.

07:17.470 --> 07:18.767
[Alex] Fuck you!

07:19.520 --> 07:20.885
You fucking rapist!

07:30.190 --> 07:33.694
Dude, shit like that
doesn't do anybody any good.

07:33.780 --> 07:35.577
Yeah? Well, it felt good to me.

07:36.160 --> 07:37.866
Maybe if you'd stop defending him
all the time.

07:37.950 --> 07:40.578
-When have I ever defended him?
-Every day.

07:40.660 --> 07:43.072
Every day you hang around him
and play baseball with him,

07:43.330 --> 07:44.456
you choose his side.

07:44.920 --> 07:45.989
Jess, tell him.

07:47.710 --> 07:49.166
Why would you do that?

07:50.260 --> 07:52.501
Shit. I'm so sorry.

07:53.630 --> 07:55.040
-I mean...
-Jess.

07:56.430 --> 07:57.385
Don't.

08:11.820 --> 08:13.697
Come on, didn't you see the red light?

08:14.200 --> 08:15.406
-It means you're not--
-Hey.

08:16.990 --> 08:17.820
Uh, hi.

08:18.870 --> 08:22.283
-Sorry.
-No, uh, you're-- No big deal.

08:22.370 --> 08:24.418
I know what the red light means.
[chuckles]

08:24.500 --> 08:26.707
So, um, last night was really fun.

08:27.670 --> 08:29.740
We should, maybe, do it again sometime.

08:29.880 --> 08:32.462
We should clean vomit
off your brother's boots?

08:32.670 --> 08:35.798
We should hang out.
Maybe not in the bathroom.

08:36.050 --> 08:38.098
So, hang out in your yard?

08:38.600 --> 08:43.549
Or another building. Restaurant.
Movie theater, perhaps?

08:44.020 --> 08:45.897
-Do you mean, like a--
-I mean, like a date.

08:47.860 --> 08:50.647
It's an early stage in the mating ritual
of homo sapiens.

08:50.940 --> 08:52.350
We agree to go somewhere together.

08:52.530 --> 08:54.020
I obsess over what to wear

08:54.110 --> 08:57.614
and then you obsess over if you should pay
or if we're splitting it.

08:58.200 --> 09:01.533
We show up,
it either goes great or it goes terrible,

09:01.700 --> 09:05.409
and then we decide if we wanna
put ourselves through It again.

09:05.750 --> 09:07.661
What sadistic person invented this ritual?

09:07.750 --> 09:08.626
[Mackenzie chuckles]

09:10.090 --> 09:10.988
Every person.

09:13.170 --> 09:15.218
-So, you wanna?
-Um...

09:16.680 --> 09:19.342
Yes. I-- I really do.

09:20.260 --> 09:22.387
She was faithful.

09:22.720 --> 09:25.302
She was kind to me
and cared about what happened to me.

09:25.520 --> 09:28.762
She never gossiped,
or told lies about people.

09:28.850 --> 09:31.603
And what sorts of things
did you do together?

09:31.690 --> 09:35.103
We had some classes together,
we ate lunch together sometimes,

09:35.490 --> 09:37.481
and we worked together at the Crestmont.

09:37.740 --> 09:39.401
And we talked, a lot.

09:39.740 --> 09:42.197
-What did you talk about?
-We talked about...

09:42.490 --> 09:47.200
about books and shows
and songs and eclipses

09:47.290 --> 09:51.784
and zombies and bike helmets and...

09:52.340 --> 09:55.832
and I guess our... our hopes and dreams.

09:56.420 --> 09:57.250
[Hannah] Helmet.

10:00.390 --> 10:02.551
Helmet. Helmet.

10:03.640 --> 10:06.382
If you don't help build this tower,
you don't get to knock it down.

10:08.230 --> 10:09.766
I-- I just need to finish this chapter.

10:10.480 --> 10:13.859
Do you really have homework?
School's over in, like, two days.

10:13.940 --> 10:16.238
All we do in my classes
is watch Stand and Deliver.

10:19.740 --> 10:25.440
I wanna get the summer reading done
before I, um, leave for my grandparents'

10:25.540 --> 10:26.404
for the summer.

10:27.330 --> 10:28.149
Wait, what?

10:29.620 --> 10:32.032
My parents think it's good
for a "growing boy"

10:32.130 --> 10:34.451
to spend time in the country. [scoffs]

10:34.550 --> 10:36.871
We don't exactly live
in a thriving metropolis.

10:38.220 --> 10:40.927
Ten minutes at my grandparents',
and you would disagree. [chuckles]

10:43.100 --> 10:45.056
What am I supposed to do all summer
without you?

10:46.430 --> 10:49.228
-Wait, you're... you're gonna miss me?
-Of course.

10:49.890 --> 10:51.300
You're the only friend I have left.

10:52.400 --> 10:53.435
Come on, that's not true.

10:55.820 --> 10:58.687
Will you write me,
like, old-school letters?

11:00.200 --> 11:03.272
Yeah. I mean, can I write them
on the computer and print them?

11:03.570 --> 11:05.902
You may not. And no postcards.

11:06.330 --> 11:10.118
_ I_want handwritten missives
filled With your deepest, darkest secrets.

11:11.250 --> 11:12.490
Are you gonna write me back?

11:13.420 --> 11:14.330
"Dear Helmet,

11:14.880 --> 11:16.950
today, someone smeared feces
on the bathroom wall,

11:17.050 --> 11:18.335
and I got to clean it up.

11:18.840 --> 11:23.083
But there was an expired box of Milk Duds
that I got to take home for free."

11:23.180 --> 11:24.966
Those are your deepest
and darkest secrets?

11:26.100 --> 11:27.510
Write me, and you'll find out.

11:30.890 --> 11:32.471
-Whoa!
-[laughs]

11:33.150 --> 11:34.299
I never wrote her.

11:38.280 --> 11:39.235
Ijust...

11:41.070 --> 11:44.562
Summer gets away from you,
and stuff happens.

11:44.950 --> 11:47.657
And I guess I didn't really think
that she'd be thinking of me.

11:47.870 --> 11:50.498
I mean, I didn't think
I was that important.

11:52.000 --> 11:55.743
And you always think that...
you think that you'll have plenty of time.

11:56.670 --> 11:57.489
[whimpers]

12:01.260 --> 12:02.158
I'm sorry.

12:08.430 --> 12:10.136
-What the hell?
-Whatever happened to

12:10.220 --> 12:12.768
"What happens in The Clubhouse
stays in The Clubhouse"?

12:12.850 --> 12:14.556
Not in here. Jesus.

12:15.520 --> 12:18.398
-What the fuck is your problem?
-Somebody's blackmailing me.

12:20.070 --> 12:21.731
If my dad sees that, I'm dead.

12:22.320 --> 12:23.275
Fuck.

12:24.530 --> 12:26.521
Look, you need to help me shut this down.

12:26.870 --> 12:29.020
-I need to?
-You owe me.

12:29.790 --> 12:31.610
I don't owe anybody anything, Marcus.

12:33.410 --> 12:35.287
I got a lot of eyes on me right now, okay?

12:35.370 --> 12:38.248
I can't get involved
in some stripper shit.

12:38.340 --> 12:41.002
-You're already involved. You were there.
-I'm not in the video.

12:41.710 --> 12:42.916
Are you fucking kidding me?

12:43.010 --> 12:45.831
After what I did for you in court,
you can't return the favor?

12:46.140 --> 12:48.677
A favor's only a favor
if someone asks for it.

12:48.760 --> 12:50.967
And I didn't ask you
to drag my name into this shit.

12:51.270 --> 12:52.089
That's on you.

12:52.430 --> 12:54.591
[school bell rings]

12:59.480 --> 13:02.358
Clay, you've testified today
that Hannah was a victim

13:02.440 --> 13:04.943
of a culture of bullying at Liberty High.

13:05.820 --> 13:08.527
But isn't it true
that you are also a part of that culture?

13:08.620 --> 13:09.905
No, I don't think I am.

13:09.990 --> 13:13.494
Isn't it true that you took pictures
of Tyler Down through his window

13:13.580 --> 13:16.617
that you then circulated around the school
via social media?

13:16.710 --> 13:18.621
-Yes, but--
-[Dennis] Objection, Your Honor.

13:18.710 --> 13:20.086
Beyond the scope of the direct.

13:20.170 --> 13:23.162
Your Honor, he's already testified
to the nature of bullying at Liberty.

13:24.010 --> 13:24.965
[judge] I'll allow it.

13:25.050 --> 13:27.678
[Sonya] Clay, isn't it true
that you were suspended from school

13:27.760 --> 13:29.079
for possession of marijuana?

13:29.180 --> 13:31.466
-It wasn't mine. I was set up.
-I see.

13:31.560 --> 13:34.131
And at any point
subsequent to that suspension,

13:34.230 --> 13:35.936
did you attempt to buy more marijuana?

13:36.690 --> 13:39.807
-Yes, but I was--
-And isn't it true that your vandalism

13:39.900 --> 13:42.607
caused thousands of dollars of damage
to Zach Dempsey's car?

13:42.690 --> 13:46.103
I was angry at him.
I... I paid for the damage.

13:46.200 --> 13:48.441
What did you do when you were angry
at Courtney Crimsen?

13:48.530 --> 13:50.020
I just took her to Hannah's grave.

13:50.280 --> 13:53.693
And isn't it true that you accused her
of being responsible for Hannah's death?

13:53.790 --> 13:56.862
She is responsible.
All of those kids are responsible.

13:56.960 --> 14:00.452
Are you responsible, Clay?
Are you responsible for Hannah's death?

14:03.710 --> 14:06.372
Yes, I am. I let her down.

14:06.920 --> 14:10.424
But there are kids who did a lot worse,
kids who you let skate,

14:10.510 --> 14:13.502
who did things you won't even talk about.
And adults at Liberty don't--

14:13.600 --> 14:15.591
[Sonya] Request to strike that
as non-responsive.

14:15.680 --> 14:18.638
[judge] So ordered.
The jury will ignore that answer.

14:18.850 --> 14:21.853
Clay, you've testified
that you were Hannah's friend

14:21.940 --> 14:22.929
but never her boyfriend.

14:23.020 --> 14:24.601
-Is that correct?
-Yes.

14:24.860 --> 14:26.600
And you said that you kissed once.

14:27.280 --> 14:28.986
-Is that correct?
-Yes.

14:29.320 --> 14:31.151
Did you ever spend a night together?

14:31.240 --> 14:35.404
You mean, have... have sex? No.

14:35.700 --> 14:39.739
No. I mean, spend a night together,

14:39.830 --> 14:42.537
evening, night, into the next morning.

14:45.210 --> 14:48.464
Clay, did you and Hannah
ever spend a night together?

14:48.920 --> 14:49.796
Yes.

14:50.050 --> 14:51.756
And did you do drugs together?

15:01.310 --> 15:02.140
Yes.

15:04.360 --> 15:06.430
-[music playing]
-[students cheering]

15:06.820 --> 15:07.935
Go, Tigers!

15:09.610 --> 15:12.568
-Hey! Go, Tigers!
-Yeah!

15:13.320 --> 15:15.447
Hey! Go, Tigers!

15:15.740 --> 15:16.616
[air horn blares]

15:18.620 --> 15:20.247
Hey! Go, Tigers!

15:22.290 --> 15:24.121
Hey! Go, Tigers!

15:24.210 --> 15:28.169
[cheering]

15:29.630 --> 15:34.465
[Chle] Let's give it up
for our varsity baseball team!

15:37.220 --> 15:39.211
[student] Go, Tigers!

15:39.640 --> 15:42.382
-[student] Oh, look at him.
-[audience] Aww.

15:42.480 --> 15:45.142
Hey, how about a hand
for our new cheer captain, Chle Rice?

15:45.230 --> 15:50.145
[cheering]

15:50.240 --> 15:51.525
So sweet.

15:52.240 --> 15:56.324
And now, for our emcee
of today's assembly,

15:56.870 --> 15:59.111
Marcus Cole!

15:59.200 --> 16:01.361
-[cheering]
-[music playing]

16:12.420 --> 16:13.250
That's right.

16:14.010 --> 16:18.504
That's right.
I, uh... dressed for the occasion.

16:18.600 --> 16:19.464
Who's impressed?

16:20.100 --> 16:22.091
[cheering]

16:28.980 --> 16:30.891
He turned it
into a fucking publicity stunt.

16:31.440 --> 16:33.351
He's got this whole
fucking school brainwashed.

16:33.450 --> 16:36.237
We have to do something else, man.
Okay? Something bigger.

16:39.030 --> 16:40.076
What did you have in mind?

16:47.000 --> 16:48.536
I'm sorry, Dad.

16:50.090 --> 16:53.082
For what, kiddo? For telling the truth?

16:54.630 --> 16:56.040
For not telling you...

16:59.010 --> 16:59.840
stuff.

17:00.390 --> 17:01.379
And what did you say?

17:01.680 --> 17:05.593
I didn't...
I didn't know what to say. I...

17:08.230 --> 17:09.766
You know there's nothing you could do,

17:11.150 --> 17:15.769
nothing that would stop your mother and me
from loving you.

17:15.990 --> 17:19.062
You heard Hannah say this,
and you did nothing?

17:19.370 --> 17:21.076
I didn't think she meant it like that.

17:23.580 --> 17:29.200
Why is it kids
don't tell their parents anything, ever?

17:31.670 --> 17:32.750
Is it shame?

17:34.380 --> 17:35.210
Or fear?

17:36.930 --> 17:40.093
It can't be fear of punishment.
No one's punished for anything anymore.

17:42.890 --> 17:44.471
Are you afraid we won't understand?

17:46.770 --> 17:49.261
More like afraid
you'd understand too well.

17:49.860 --> 17:51.396
So you're protecting your secrets?

17:51.900 --> 17:54.391
We were all still recovering--

17:54.610 --> 17:58.023
From drugs.
And that explains why you did nothing?

17:59.160 --> 18:00.445
Or we're protecting you.

18:06.870 --> 18:08.201
Look, I have to get to school.

18:13.420 --> 18:17.254
_ Let's welcome
this year's varSIty track team!

18:18.300 --> 18:20.712
-[students cheering]
-[music playing]

18:32.110 --> 18:37.104
[Clay] Hey, Slqe. Me again.
Court was not great.

18:38.740 --> 18:41.231
They found out about this thing
Hannah said one time,

18:41.320 --> 18:43.481
and they blew it way out of proportion.

18:47.580 --> 18:50.788
But now I can't stop thinking
about the morning she said it

18:51.170 --> 18:52.876
and the night we spent before.

18:53.380 --> 18:54.369
