40:11.240 --> 40:13.606
Hey, Mom.
Yeah, no, I'm just out with the guys.

40:16.080 --> 40:19.243
I'll be home soon.
Yeah. No, I know, I know.

40:21.370 --> 40:22.200
[sighs]

40:22.290 --> 40:25.248
Okay. Yeah, I'm on my way. Bye.

40:28.710 --> 40:29.665
"The guys"?

40:31.050 --> 40:32.210
You're out with the guys?

40:32.840 --> 40:34.580
I just told her I'd go home and watch May.

40:34.680 --> 40:35.544
Home from what?

40:35.970 --> 40:37.380
Why'd you lie about where you are?

40:38.010 --> 40:38.920
I wasn't sure--

40:39.100 --> 40:41.011
Of course you should lie to her
and everybody

40:41.100 --> 40:43.261
'cause that's better than admitting
you're my friend?

40:43.350 --> 40:45.398
-She knows you're my friend.
-Bryce know where you are?

40:45.480 --> 40:47.016
-Come on, man.
-Fuck you, Zach.

40:47.110 --> 40:48.316
-Okay.
-Go home.

40:50.230 --> 40:52.232
Yeah, I should. Um...

40:53.070 --> 40:55.903
-Thank you guys for having me.
-[Deputy Standall] You don't have to go.

40:59.540 --> 41:01.440
I'm gonna go play some games.

41:07.630 --> 41:10.201
All right, you guys, truth now.
What the hell's going on?

41:10.670 --> 41:11.659
He's not all right.

41:14.090 --> 41:15.170
Uh... [clears throat]

41:16.680 --> 41:19.638
I think he does pretty well, most days.

41:19.720 --> 41:21.176
Bullshit. You said he made progress.

41:21.270 --> 41:23.261
He hasn't made any
since the day I saw him last.

41:23.350 --> 41:24.886
-A month ago.
-[Mrs. Standall] He's trying.

41:24.980 --> 41:26.186
Oh, he's really trying.

41:30.020 --> 41:31.226
Oh, shit.

41:31.320 --> 41:33.481
[loud game gunfire]

41:36.780 --> 41:37.610
Hey, buddy.

41:38.660 --> 41:41.288
-What are you doing?
-Just playing a game, Dad.

41:42.910 --> 41:45.208
Okay, maybe this isn't the right game
to be playing now.

41:45.290 --> 41:47.360
Why not? I'm really good at it.

41:48.460 --> 41:50.166
Let's play another round of Skee-Ball--

41:50.250 --> 41:51.911
-No, Dad, fuck that.
-Alex.

41:59.850 --> 42:01.340
[game gunfire echoes]

42:04.930 --> 42:07.012
-Give me this thing. That's enough.
-Fuck, no.

42:07.100 --> 42:08.055
Fuck, no!

42:09.400 --> 42:12.142
-All right, buddy, I'm sorry. Come here.
-Fucking let me go!

42:14.570 --> 42:16.731
I'm broken, okay?

42:21.240 --> 42:22.537
I'm fucking broken.

42:22.870 --> 42:25.407
That's how it's gonna be.
Why don't you just live with it?

42:25.500 --> 42:27.957
-Alex, you're not broken.
-How the fuck would you know?

42:28.250 --> 42:30.571
I've seen you twice
since I got out of the hospital.

42:30.880 --> 42:33.371
-I had school.
-I had fucking school, too!

42:35.260 --> 42:36.579
And I had friends.

42:38.220 --> 42:39.380
Now I don't have anything,

42:40.390 --> 42:42.631
except all of you standing around
feeling sorry for me,

42:43.180 --> 42:44.716
not fucking knowing what to say.

42:45.470 --> 42:47.631
Maybe it would've been better
if it'd worked.

42:48.310 --> 42:49.720
Put the bullet through my brain

42:49.810 --> 42:51.357
-the way it was supposed to go?
-Stop.

42:51.730 --> 42:52.810
Wouldn't that be better?

42:53.020 --> 42:55.102
You could get on
with your stupid fucking lives.

42:55.190 --> 42:57.852
Fuck you, Alex. Okay? Shut up.
Just shut up.

42:57.950 --> 42:58.848
-Jess.
-No.

42:58.950 --> 43:00.690
Listen to me, you asshole.

43:00.990 --> 43:02.230
How could you do what you did?

43:02.450 --> 43:05.328
After Hannah, I needed you.

43:05.580 --> 43:08.242
You were the only one I could trust,
who understood

43:08.330 --> 43:11.128
